ickering";s:4:"slug";s:28:"garage-door-light-flickering";s:5:"title";s:34:"How To Repair A Garage Door Opener";s:3:"alt";s:9:"pinterest";s:3:"url";s:76:"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/46/02/58/4602580996692a9e81537e8cb9224398.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:123:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcS0_y_0NGSLZfMqAUf1yDU98fmmPhyZmsyMvYJuHLKJijhWsZtyZcQxdPe0FS5j2woh7f8";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:350;s:6:"height";i:285;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/281826889160528716/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}i:19;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:28:"garage door light flickering";s:4:"slug";s:28:"garage-door-light-flickering";s:5:"title";s:71:"Garage Opener Light Blinking A Troubleshooting Guide Garage Door Medics";s:3:"alt";s:18:"garage door medics";s:3:"url";s:73:"https://gdmedics.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/safetysensors-300x122.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:122:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTZGqW8pLn4UyXFREMEHE44J4QMTEBz_kwJVwC4-QZmpdL_du2RzsOF2HtK9tOzW-adwA";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:122;s:6:"height";i:300;s:6:"source";s:50:"https://gdmedics.com/garage-opener-light-blinking/";s:6:"domain";s:12:"gdmedics.com";}i:20;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:28:"garage door light flickering";s:4:"slug";s:28:"garage-door-light-flickering";s:5:"title";s:66:"Garage Door Opener Is Blinking Red And Won T Close Homeimprovement";s:3:"alt";s:6:"reddit";s:3:"url";s:133:"https://external-preview.redd.it/KVHO2nmBV6SF7TevBzA50KpoJ5ee9wB_C4fwHBw1DkU.jpg?auto=webp&s=22632d0df2a2d37384292265e6fabf89d7a9af7e";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQfps8oKpCxp8UTpc8mFR4Q2lvirXdCNOrq6Q";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:4032;s:6:"height";i:3024;s:6:"source";s:107:"https://www.reddit.com/r/HomeImprovement/comments/6jxl34/garage_door_opener_is_blinking_red_and_wont_close/";s:6:"domain";s:14:"www.reddit.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:67:{i:0;s:135:"Having your garage door light blink continuously is not only annoying its also a sign that there is something wrong with the mechanism.";i:1;s:68:"There are several reasons why your garage door opener is doing this.";i:2;s:119:"However the two most common reasons include a problem with the lock button and malfunctioning safety reversing sensors.";i:3;s:189:"If you continue having problems with your garage door light blinking after having tried these solutions the issue may be related to the logic board or a malfunction with the internal parts.";i:4;s:137:"Contact Garage Door Medics today by calling 888-997-2423 so that we can diagnose your issue and get your garage door back up and running.";i:5;s:52:"What does blinking light on garage door opener mean.";i:6;s:84:"One flash indicates that your safety sensor wire may be open broken or disconnected.";i:7;s:116:"If your opener flashes twice then your sensor wire is either shorted or the black and white wires could be reversed.";i:8;s:79:"If the sensors are aligned and the lights glow then the wires need replacement.";i:9;s:44:"Why is my garage door sensor blinking green.";i:10;s:96:"Green lights mean the sensors are working while red lights indicate the sensors are not aligned.";i:11;s:94:"If you see red lights try inspecting the bracket or tightening a screw on the blinking sensor.";i:12;s:103:"Youll know you fixed the sensor if the light stops blinking and your garage door closes properly again.";i:13;s:43:"Why is my garage door wall switch blinking.";i:14;s:148:"A blinking light on the garage door sensor isn t really cause for alarm but it does let the homeowner know that something s not working quite right.";i:15;s:220:"Garage door opener light blinks led light blinking indicates a problem note the led light that is referred to in this article is the small light that is located on the opener near the adjustment learn or program buttons.";i:16;s:44:"Why is my garage door sensor blinking green.";i:17;s:87:"The amber light on the sending sensor will glow regardless of alignment or obstruction.";i:18;s:194:"Meaning this light will always be on no matter what If the green light on the receiving sensor is off dim or flickering and the invisible light beam path is not obstructed alignment is required.";i:19;s:51:"Now insert a light bulb and plug the power back in.";i:20;s:25:"The bulb should light up.";i:21;s:57:"If it does remove the light bulb and go to the next step.";i:22;s:54:"If the bulb does not light up you may have a bad bulb.";i:23;s:52:"Try another bulb or test the bulb with an ohm meter.";i:24;s:32:"Now unplug the power to the GDO.";i:25;s:44:"Reinserting the light socket into the panel.";i:26;s:54:"Simply so why is my garage door opener light flashing.";i:27;s:99:"The blinking opener lights indicate that the safety sensors are likely blocked or out of alignment.";i:28;s:96:"Defective safety sensors or faulty sensor wiring also cause the opener lights to blink 10 times.";i:29;s:107:"The safety sensors use an invisible beam of infrared light to detect obstructions in the garage doors path.";i:30;s:44:"Why is my garage door sensor blinking green.";i:31;s:96:"Green lights mean the sensors are working while red lights indicate the sensors are not aligned.";i:32;s:94:"If you see red lights try inspecting the bracket or tightening a screw on the blinking sensor.";i:33;s:103:"Youll know you fixed the sensor if the light stops blinking and your garage door closes properly again.";i:34;s:127:"Faulty sensors occur due to damaged wires or dirty lenses and you may wonder the cause of your garage door sensor blinking red.";i:35;s:54:"The exterior LED light blinks when the door is closed.";i:36;s:158:"The green light shows that the sensors are working while the red blinking light indicates the sensors are not aligned and there is a fault in the garage door.";i:37;s:148:"When you see your garage door opener lights flashing and the garage door will not close it could be the safety reversing sensors or the LOCK button.";i:38;s:75:"If there is a safety reversing sensor issue the main lights flash 10 times.";i:39;s:39:"Start with aligning the safety sensors.";i:40;s:111:"You can close the garage door by pressing and holding the door control push bar until down travel is completed.";i:41;s:139:"My liftmaster did this repeatedly driving me nuts even after pulling out on that center contact tab at the bottom of the light bulb socket.";i:42;s:51:"Itd work for a while and then revert to flickering.";i:43;s:47:"If the bulb was overtightened it wouldnt light.";i:44;s:70:"If it was undertightened it would light but soon revert to flickering.";i:45;s:49:"Why is the Genie garage door sensor flashing red.";i:46;s:59:"The sensors are not aligned as indicated by the red lights.";i:47;s:79:"If you notice a red light check the bracket or tighten the blink sensors screw.";i:48;s:104:"You will know you have fixed the sensor if the light stops flashing and the garage door closes properly.";i:49;s:43:"Why is the garage door keypad flashing red.";i:50;s:31:"Contact the wires collectively.";i:51;s:52:"If the door is operating alternate the door control.";i:52;s:75:"If the door does not work there is a need to update the door control wires.";i:53;s:29:"LED light flashes four times.";i:54;s:146:"Clean the protective sensor lenses and reset them if the LED lights up four times before it stops that is an indication of an incompatible sensor.";i:55;s:71:"Consequently what does it mean when the garage door opener is blinking.";i:56;s:164:"The most common reason for the lights to flash on the garage door opener and the door not closing is that the safety reversing sensors are misaligned or obstructed.";i:57;s:44:"This is a safety feature of the garage door.";i:58;s:113:"Today were going to talk about troubleshooting a garage door opener that wont close the door and blinks 10 times.";i:59;s:99:"The blinking opener lights indicate that the safety sensors are likely blocked or out of alignment.";i:60;s:78:"Defective safety sensors or faulty sensor wiring 